OL,3,CMan admits mocking stadium disaster
OL,4,Cand racist abuse at Merseyside derby
OL,6,FSenior crown prosecutor Angela Conlan
OL,7,Fof CPS Mersey Cheshire said: "Joel
OL,8,FBarwise no doubt thinks of himself as
OL,9,Fa loyal Everton fan, but his actions
OL,10,Fbring shame to his club.
OL,12,F"He made fun of a tragic football
OL,13,Fdisaster in Turin in 1985 and shouted
OL,14,Fracist abuse when a key Liverpool
OL,15,Fplayer's name was announced.
OL,17,F"Football has no place for this sort
OL,18,Fof behaviour and the majority of
OL,19,FEverton fans would no doubt condemn
OL,20,Fhis actions on that day and want to
OL,21,Fdisassociate themselves from them.
